# src/domain/

The **domain layer** — pure business logic with no I/O, no framework
dependencies, and no awareness of how it's persisted or served.

Belongs here:
- Entities (objects with identity that change over time)
- Value objects (immutable, equality by value)
- Aggregates and their roots
- Domain services (business operations that don't naturally fit on an entity)
- Domain events
- Repository **interfaces** (the contract; the implementation lives in `../infrastructure/`)

Does **not** belong here:
- ORM models, SQL, HTTP clients, file I/O — those go in `../infrastructure/`
- Use-case orchestration, transactions, command/query handlers — those go in `../application/`
- Anything that imports a framework

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/ddd.md`. The
layering rules live in `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/architecture.md`.
